About TestRail test cases management tool
Features


TestRail is a test case management tool used in software testing to plan, organize, execute, and track testing activities. It helps QA teams manage manual and 
automated tests, monitor progress, and report quality status clearly to stakeholders.

1. What is TestRail?

  TestRail is a web-based test management system that allows teams to:
  
  Store and organize test cases
  
  Create test plans and test runs
  
  Execute tests and record results
  
  Track defects by integrating with bug-tracking tools
  
  Generate reports and metrics

Features of TestRaill
  1. Test Case Management
    Create, edit, and organize test cases
    Group test cases into sections (Login, Checkout, Payments, etc.)
    Reuse test cases across projects

  2. Test Plans: It defines like how it will be started, what will be tested and which configurations are used
  3. Test Runs: A test run is where the testsers actually executes the test cases
  4. Defect Tracking Integration: it integrate defects with tools like Jira, Bugzilla, Github Issues etc.
  5. Reporting and metrics

  6. User roles and admins
    It defines access levels and secutiry based on the role like admin, test manager, tester and viewer



Typically testrail workflow follows like:
create project -> create milestone, sections and subsections -> create test cases -> create test runs -> create test plans -> execute tests -> log defects -> show reports and metrics
